1. NEAREST-NEIGHBOR always — viewport scaling must never be bilinear or Lanczos. GPU upscales for free.
2. Internal resolution: 720x540 (4:3), pillarboxed on widescreen. Scales cleanly to 1440x1080 (2x) and 2880x2160 (4x). Do not change without deliberate art direction review.
3. Draw calls ≤50 per frame. Memory ≤256MB total, ≤64MB textures.
4. Aseprite (.aseprite) is the canonical art format — PNG sprite sheets are exports. CLI export: aseprite -b --sheet out.png --data out.json in.aseprite. All exports use snake_case matching GDScript class names.
